commitResults.messageBody:
Add test scripts for TagCommand and TagCommandParser

TagCommand and TagCommandParser currently lack dedicated test scripts, making it difficult to verify their correctness and ensure they work as expected.

Add unit tests for TagCommand and TagCommandParser using JUnit. Cover various input cases, including valid and invalid inputs, to ensure robustness.

Testing is done this way to improve code reliability and prevent regressions when modifying the command logic. The approach follows existing testing conventions in the project.

This change enhances test coverage and simplifies debugging by catching issues early.

Add test scripts for SavePreferenceCommand, Preference, and SavePreferenceCommandParser

SavePreferenceCommand, Preference, and SavePreferenceCommandParser lack dedicated test scripts, making it difficult to verify their correctness and ensure they function as intended.

Add unit tests for SavePreferenceCommand, Preference, and SavePreferenceCommandParser using JUnit. Test various scenarios, including valid and invalid preference values, to ensure robustness.

This approach follows the project's existing testing framework, ensuring consistency and maintainability. Comprehensive testing helps prevent regressions and improves reliability.

This change enhances test coverage, making debugging and future modifications easier.
Debug and add tests for viewOrders
Fix PersonBuilder.java and add tests to findOrders
Change person to customer in User Guide
Add more information to user guide
Add more information to user guide

Update model class diagrams

The model class diagrams are outdated and do not accurately reflect recent changes in the codebase, making them less useful for documentation and understanding the system design.

Update the model class diagrams to align with the latest implementation. Modify class relationships, attributes, and methods as needed to match the current structure.

This ensures that the documentation remains accurate and useful for developers working on the project. Keeping diagrams up to date helps with onboarding and system maintenance.

This change improves clarity and prevents confusion caused by outdated documentation.

Improve code coverage of JsonAdaptedPerson (add test cases)

The current test coverage for JsonAdaptedPerson is insufficient, leaving potential edge cases untested and reducing confidence in its correctness.

Add additional unit tests for JsonAdaptedPerson to cover various scenarios, including valid and invalid JSON inputs, missing fields, and boundary cases.

This ensures that JsonAdaptedPerson behaves as expected under different conditions, improving robustness and preventing potential errors. The approach follows the project's existing testing framework for consistency.

This change enhances test coverage, making the codebase more reliable and maintainable.

Update ViewOrdersCommand to include frequency of dishes ordered

The ViewOrdersCommand does not display the frequency of each dish ordered, making it harder to analyze popular items efficiently.

Modify ViewOrdersCommand to compute and display the frequency of each dish ordered. Update relevant data structures and UI components accordingly.

This change improves usability by providing better insights into ordering trends. The implementation follows existing data-handling patterns for consistency and maintainability.

This enhancement makes it easier to track popular dishes and aids decision-making for menu optimization.
Fix code style to pass checkstyle tests

Ensure AddOrderCommand rejects empty dish names with only spaces

AddOrderCommand allows dish names consisting only of spaces, which can lead to inconsistent data and unintended behavior.

Modify AddOrderCommand to validate dish names and raise a CommandException if the input consists only of whitespace.

This ensures data integrity by preventing invalid entries. The validation approach follows existing input checks in the command structure for consistency.

This change improves robustness and prevents erroneous order entries in the system.
